Aw man. I had this anti-troll strategy I'd use that relied on the anonymous pings. When somebody would get mad and start pinging another person's build, I'd ping other things on our team at random in between them so it looked like one person was just spam-pinging with no purpose at all.

Nobody had time to argue about builds with pings because the information overload of all the random pings between the real ones. Oh well, its probably better this way. Now you can mute anyone that gets too ping-happy.

{{sticker:poppy-wink}}

That moment when an amumu main thinks roa is good on amumu 
{{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}} 

Thinking all champ mains know the optimal build for their champions is delusional.
